Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Remove the top and bottom from the @carrot{2} and @baby parsnip{1}. Chop into batons the size of your little finger (no need to peel). Pop on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle over a glug of @olive oil{}. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and a good grinding of @black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} into half moons. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}. Pick the @tarragon{} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Keep the two herbs separate. Drain and rinse the @brown lentils{1%cup} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the onion. Cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @red wine vinegar{1%tbsp} and allow to evaporate completely before stirring in the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and the @water{100%ml}. Simmer until the stock has reduced by half, about ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice the @ciabatta{1} into 2cm chunks and place on another baking tray. Drizzle over a glug of @olive oil{}, sprinkle on the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and season with a good grind of @black pepper{}. Toss together. Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Once the stock has reduced, stir in the @baby spinach{1%handful}, lentils and @creme fraiche{1%tbsp}. Bring to a simmer and cook until the spinach has wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}. > Stir a few times whilst this is happening to ensure the spinach wilts evenly. Add the @wholegrain mustard{1%tbsp} and parsley then remove from the heat. Season to taste with salt and black pepper.

Remove the roasted veggies from the oven. Squeeze the @honey{1%tbsp} over them and sprinkle on the tarragon. Toss to coat. Spoon the lentils into #bowls{}, top with the roasted veggies and sprinkle on the @walnuts{25}. Scatter over the cheesy croutons and enjoy!